From c18ac65c76ca276fcf04c8582137becba84f8a17 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Marcello Sylvester Bauer <marcello.bauer@9elements.com>
Date: Thu, 8 Jan 2026 01:20:02 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 4/8] arm: gxp: add KCS and SSIF IPMI BMC drivers

Add IPMI interface drivers for the HPE GXP BMC:

- kcs_bmc_gxp: KCS (Keyboard Controller Style) BMC interface driver
  for IPMI communication with the host system

- ssif_bmc: SSIF (SMBus System Interface) BMC driver core providing
  the common infrastructure for SSIF-based IPMI communication

- ssif_bmc_gxp: GXP-specific SSIF BMC implementation

These drivers enable IPMI communication between the BMC and the host
system using either the KCS or SSIF transport protocols.

Signed-off-by: Marcello Sylvester Bauer <marcello.bauer@9elements.com>

